    build: consolidate jsc:build into build.ts, add BUN_WEBKIT_PATH (#28863)
    
    ## What
    
    `jsc:build*` scripts now route through `scripts/build.ts
    --profile=*-local --target=WebKit` instead of the standalone
    `scripts/build-jsc.ts`.
    
    `$BUN_WEBKIT_PATH` lets worktrees share one WebKit clone instead of
    cloning `vendor/WebKit/` per worktree.
    
    ## Why
    
    `scripts/build-jsc.ts` duplicated toolchain/platform detection and cmake
    invocation that `scripts/build/deps/webkit.ts` already handles in local
    mode (`build:local` uses this today). The seven extra cmake flags it
    passed were checked against WebKit source:
    `ENABLE_SINGLE_THREADED_VM_ENTRY_SCOPE`, `BUN_FAST_TLS`,
    `JSEXPORT_PRIVATE` have zero hits; `PTHREAD_JIT_PERMISSIONS_API`,
    `USE_PTHREAD_JIT_PERMISSIONS_API`, `USE_VISIBILITY_ATTRIBUTE` are
    preprocessor-only defines auto-set in `PlatformUse.h` (not cmake vars);
    `USE_SYSTEM_MALLOC` is a real option but webkit.ts builds Windows fine
    without it.
    
    WebKit is a ~10min clone, so requiring `vendor/WebKit/` per worktree is
    impractical.
    
    ## Changes
    
    - `package.json`: `jsc:build` / `jsc:build:debug` / `jsc:build:lto` →
    `build.ts --profile={release,debug,release}-local [--lto=on]
    --target=WebKit`
    - `scripts/build-jsc.ts`: deleted
    - `scripts/build/source.ts`: `kind: "local"` sources can now specify
    `path` (override `vendor/<name>/`) and `hint` (custom not-found message)
    - `scripts/build/deps/webkit.ts`: reads `$BUN_WEBKIT_PATH` (with `~`
    expansion, repo-root-anchored relative paths); not-found hint mentions
    the env var
    - `scripts/build/clean.ts`: removed `vendor/WebKit/WebKitBuild/`
    references — local WebKit now builds into
    `build/<profile>/deps/WebKit/`, which the profile preset already cleans
    
    ## Workflow
    
    ```sh
    # one-time, per machine
    export BUN_WEBKIT_PATH=~/code/bun/vendor/WebKit  # in ~/.zshenv
    
    # in any worktree
    bun run build:local       # Bun + local WebKit
    bun run jsc:build:debug   # just WebKit
    ```
    
    ## Verified
    
    tsc passes; `bun scripts/build.ts --profile=debug-local
    --target=configure-WebKit` runs cmake configure successfully with
    `BUN_WEBKIT_PATH` pointing at a shared clone; not-found error shows the
    new hint; `clean.ts --dry-run` for all presets works; prebuilt-webkit
    configure path unchanged.
    
    ---------
    
    Co-authored-by: autofix-ci[bot] <114827586+autofix-ci[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>

