commit 196ed8a1bd4d5c9915e71816ce64a6a281eee23e
Author: Dylan Conway <dylan.conway567@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 6 20:21:08 2026 -0700

    http: reject conflicting duplicate Content-Length headers (#28838)
    
    ## Summary
    - Per RFC 9112 §6.3, multiple `Content-Length` header fields are only
    valid if every value is identical; otherwise the message is ambiguous
    and must be rejected to prevent request smuggling.
    - `HttpParser.h` previously only inspected the first `Content-Length`
    via `getHeader()`, silently ignoring conflicting duplicates. After
    parsing headers, the parser now walks every `Content-Length` header and
    returns `400` with `HTTP_PARSER_ERROR_INVALID_CONTENT_LENGTH` if any
    value differs byte-for-byte from the first.
    - The extra loop only runs when a `Content-Length` is present, so the
    common path is unchanged.
    
    ## Test plan
    - [x] `bun bd test test/js/bun/http/request-smuggling.test.ts` — 52
    pass, 0 fail
    - [x] New test `rejects conflicting duplicate Content-Length headers`
    fails on system bun (request accepted with 200) and passes on the debug
    build
    - [x] New test `accepts duplicate Content-Length headers with identical
    values` passes on both
    - [x] Existing `rejects Transfer-Encoding + Content-Length` test still
    passes (new check runs first but doesn't short-circuit
    single-Content-Length requests)

